    "ideation": "The MiniDisc animation personifies the physical act of digital/optical reading. The face acts as the hardware: eyes are the laser lens, and the mouth is the high-speed data stream. The animation begins with a 'loading' sequence where the eyes mechanically center and narrow to focus. As the disc spins up, the mouth transforms from a flat idle line into a high-frequency digital jitter. The climax involves a 'seek' operation where the eyes snap horizontally (simulating the laser head moving across tracks) while the data-mouth ripples with information. The color palette uses retro tech-indigo and a signature shimmering magenta/cyan to evoke the interference patterns on a magneto-optical disc surface.",
